#. Tag: title
#: vm_security.xml:321
#, no-c-format
msgid "Current limitations"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:323
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following limitations are placed on SEV-SNP &vmguest;s."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:329
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The guest operating system running inside an SEV-SNP protected VM must "
"contain SEV-SNP support. &sls; 15 SP6 and newer releases support SEV-SNP."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:335
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SEV-SNP protected &vmguest;s cannot be installed with <command>virt-install</"
"command> via ISO using the <option>--cdrom</option> option. Use the "
"<option>--location</option> instead. See the <command>virt-install</command> "
"manual page for more information on the <option>--location</option> option."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:343
#, no-c-format
msgid "SEV-SNP protected &vmguest;s support a maximum of 255 vCPUs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:348
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SEV-SNP protected &vmguest;s are not compatible with Secure Boot. UEFI "
"firmware containing Secure Boot support does not work with SEV-SNP &vmguest;"
"s."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:354
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\t SEV-SNP protected &vmguest;s are not compatible with &vmhost;-provided "
"TPM\t devices. This includes emulated and passthrough TPM devices.\t"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:360
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SEV-SNP protected Direct &vmguest;s do not support pass-through of host "
"devices\t (PCI passthrough)."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:366
#, no-c-format
msgid "SEV-SNP protected &vmguest;s do not support memory ballooning."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:371
#, no-c-format
msgid "SEV-SNP protected &vmguest;s do not support memory or vCPU hotplugging."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:376
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using hugepages within a SEV-SNP protected &vmguest; is not supported."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:381
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"SEV-SNP &vmguest;s cannot be rebooted from within using <command>reboot</"
"command> ,\t <command>shutdown -r now</command> , etc. A reboot must be done "
"by shutting down the\t &vmguest; and starting it again."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:388
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Any operations that involve saving and restoring the memory and state of a\t "
"&vmguest; are currently not supported. This means that SEV-SNP protected\t "
"&vmguest;s cannot be resumed from snapshots, saved/restored or live migrated."
"\t SEV-SNP protected &vmguest;s can be shut down and restarted on another "
"host."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: vm_security.xml:397
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These limitations may be removed in the future as the hardware, firmware and "
"specific layers of software receive new features."
msgstr ""

